---
title: Lobster-Filled Ravioli & Scallops with Sherry Shallot Cream Sauce, Tomatoes & Herbs
description: When tender ravioli are packed with fresh lobster and pillowy ricotta, then topped with succulent, seared scallops, we call that a crustacean celebration! This divine dish is kicked up a notch with a sherry and shallot cream sauce, and a sprinkle of fresh herbs and grape tomatoes. We won’t call you shellfish for licking the plate clean.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/lobster-filled-ravioli-scallops-9cfd4da0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/lobster-filled-ravioli-scallops-61670c08115a0221c037a65e-93f74f38.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1480 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/lobster-filled-ravioli-scallops-61670c08115a0221c037a65e
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Peel and mince @garlic{2%clove}. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Finely chop @green herb blend{1}.

Pat @scallops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over high heat. Add scallops to hot pan; spread out in an even layer and cook, without stirring, until opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Once water is boiling, gently add @lobster ravioli{9%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for scallops over medium-high heat. Stir in shallot, garlic, and tomatoes; season with salt and pepper. Cook until shallot is translucent and tomatoes are softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Add half the @sherry vinegar{5%teaspoon} (all for 4) and cook, stirring, until vinegar has mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @seafood stock concentrate{1}, and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings) to pan with sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4) until melted and smooth.

Gently stir in drained ravioli, scallops, and half the herbs. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Garnish with remaining herbs and serve.